Event.info: Incident - pear.php.net - compromised and delivering malicious package

Object.description: Microblog post like a Twitter tweet or a post on a Facebook wall.
Object.name: microblog

Attribute.value: A security breach has been found on the http://pear.php.net  webserver, with a tainted go-pear.phar discovered. The PEAR website itself has been disabled until a known clean site can be rebuilt. A more detailed announcement will be on the PEAR Blog once it's back online.

Object.description: File object describing a file with meta-information
Object.name: file

Object.description: Object describing a computer program written to be run in a special run-time environment. The script or shell script can be used for malicious activities but also as support tools for threat analysts.
Object.name: script
